          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 26:29-33",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " gives the same line with additions thus:—",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This last passage is important, because it expressly declares that the names all represent clans, with the exception of Zelophehad, who “had no sons, but daughters.” It also shows that Asriel was great-grandson of Manasseh. The parenthesis of 1Chronicles 7:14, therefore, appears to be intended to warn the reader that Asriel was the “son” of the Aramean concubine of Manasseh, mediately through descent from Machir.",
        "children": [
