    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The sons of Manasseh; Ashriel, whom she bare,.... The wife of Manasseh, as distinguished from his concubine in the next clause; though the Targum reads, in connection with that,\"whom his Aramitess (or Syrian) concubine bare;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and then adds: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "who also bare Machir the father of Gilead; so that Ashriel and Machir were brethren; from which Ashriel sprung the family of the Ashrielites, Numbers 26:29 as from Machir the Machirites, Numbers 26:29. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "who also bare Machir the father of Gilead; so that Ashriel and Machir were brethren; from which Ashriel sprung the family of the Ashrielites, ",
